{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_011bwy6FqmfZHwn51sRPpQG8","type":"tool_result","content":"   150→      title: \"Custom Wagers\",\n   151→      content: `TAUNT lets you choose your own wager amount for every game.\n   152→\n   153→Wager limits:\n   154→• Minimum: 0.001 SOL\n   155→• Maximum: 100 SOL\n   156→\n   157→How it works:\n   158→• Enter any amount within the limits before joining a game\n   159→• In head-to-head games (Flip You), both players wager the same amount\n   160→• In pool games (Lord of RNGs, Close Call), your share of the pool scales with your wager\n   161→\n   162→Benefits:\n   163→• Play at exactly the stake you're comfortable with\n   164→• No fixed tiers — full flexibility\n   165→• Preset buttons for quick common amounts`\n   166→    },\n   167→    {\n   168→      id: \"leaderboard\",\n   169→      title: \"Leaderboard System\",\n   170→      content: `Leaderboard system details coming soon.\n   171→\n   172→We're working on implementing competitive leaderboards to track and reward top players. Stay tuned for updates!`\n   173→    },\n   174→    {\n   175→      id: \"fairness\",\n   176→      title: \"On-Chain Fairness\",\n   177→      content: `All game outcomes are provably fair using cryptographic verification:\n   178→\n   179→Commit-Reveal Pattern (Crash, Close Call):\n   180→1. Server publishes a hash of its seed before betting\n   181→2. Solana blockhash becomes the public seed\n   182→3. After the round, server reveals its seed\n   183→4. Anyone can verify the outcome matches\n   184→\n   185→On-Chain VRF (Jackpot, Flip You):\n   186→1. Game requests randomness from VRF provider\n   187→2. VRF generates verifiable random bytes\n   188→3. Result and proof stored on Solana blockchain\n   189→4. Anyone can verify using blockchain explorer\n   190→\n   191→Visit the Fairness page in the header for verification tools.`\n   192→    },\n   193→    {\n   194→      id: \"rng-buff\",\n   195→      title: \"Heater\",\n   196→      content: `The Heater is a powerful temporary bonus granted to players who help drop the Mark before the timer expires.\n   197→\n   198→How to get the Heater:\n   199→1. Participate in the hourly Dogpile Raid by wagering in any game\n   200→2. Your wagers land \"hits\" on the Mark\n   201→3. If the Mark is dropped before time runs out, ALL participants receive the Heater\n   202→4. The Heater lasts for 1 hour (until the next raid starts)\n   203→\n   204→Heater Benefits:\n   205→• Golden glowing border on your avatar (visible to all players)\n   206→• Chance to drop crates when wagering\n   207→• Drop chance scales with wager amount (1% base + 5% per SOL, max 25%)\n   208→\n   209→Visual Indicators:\n   210→• Golden pulsing border around your avatar everywhere in the app\n   211→• Heater icon with countdown timer in your profile header\n   212→• Star icon with timer in the main header\n   213→\n   214→The Heater expires when the next raid begins, so make the most of it!`\n   215→    },\n   216→    {\n   217→      id: \"treasure-chests\",\n   218→      title: \"Crates\",\n   219→      content: `Crates are mystery rewards that contain XP and SOL prizes. Open them in the Loot page.\n   220→\n   221→How to earn crates:\n   222→• Heater drops: Random chance when wagering with active Heater\n   223→• Complete ALL daily quests: 1 crate\n   224→• Complete weekly quests: 1 crate per quest (3 total)\n   225→• Complete ALL weekly quests: +2 bonus crates (5 total)\n   226→\n   227→Heater crate drop rates:\n   228→• Base chance: 1% per wager\n   229→• Bonus: +5% per 1 SOL wagered\n   230→• Maximum: 25% chance per wager\n   231→\n   232→Crate rarity (determined when opened):\n   233→• Common (50%): 50-100 XP, 0.001-0.005 SOL\n   234→• Uncommon (30%): 100-250 XP, 0.005-0.01 SOL\n   235→• Rare (15%): 250-500 XP, 0.01-0.025 SOL\n   236→• Epic (4%): 500-1000 XP, 0.025-0.05 SOL\n   237→• Legendary (1%): 1000-2500 XP, 0.05-0.1 SOL\n   238→\n   239→SOL rewards are paid from the platform treasury. May the RNG gods smile upon you!`\n   240→    },\n   241→  ];\n   242→\n   243→  return (\n   244→    <>\n   245→      <footer className=\"footer-v2\">\n   246→        <div className=\"ft-logo\">TAUNT<em>.</em></div>\n   247→        <div className=\"ft-links\">\n   248→          <button type=\"button\" className=\"ft-lnk\" onClick={() => setShowFAQ(true)}>FAQ</button>\n   249→          <button type=\"button\" className=\"ft-lnk\" onClick={() => setShowTerms(true)}>Terms</button>\n   250→          <a href=\"https://x.com/rngutopia\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" className=\"ft-lnk\">Twitter</a>\n   251→          <a href=\"https://t.me/rngutopia\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" className=\"ft-lnk\">Telegram</a>\n   252→        </div>\n   253→        <div className=\"ft-tag\">taunt.bet &middot; Provably Fair &middot; Solana</div>\n   254→      </footer>\n   255→\n   256→      {/* Terms Modal */}\n   257→      {showTerms && (\n   258→        <div className=\"footer-terms-overlay\">\n   259→          <div className=\"footer-terms-modal\" ref={termsModalRef}>\n   260→            <button\n   261→              type=\"button\"\n   262→              className=\"footer-terms-close\"\n   263→              onClick={() => setShowTerms(false)}\n   264→            >\n   265→              ×\n   266→            </button>\n   267→            <h3 className=\"footer-terms-title\">Terms of Use</h3>\n   268→            <div className=\"footer-terms-content\">\n   269→              <p>\n   270→                By accessing and using TAUNT, you confirm that you are not a citizen,\n   271→                resident, or located within any jurisdiction where online gambling is prohibited\n   272→                or restricted by law, including but not limited to: the United States,\n   273→                United Kingdom, France, Germany, Spain, the Netherlands, or any other\n   274→                jurisdiction with similar regulations.\n   275→              </p>\n   276→              <p>\n   277→                You are solely responsible for determining whether your use of this platform\n   278→                is lawful in your country or region of residence. TAUNT does not provide\n   279→                legal advice and assumes no liability for users who access the platform in\n   280→                violation of applicable laws.\n   281→              </p>\n   282→              <p>\n   283→                By continuing to use this service, you acknowledge and accept these terms.\n   284→              </p>\n   285→            </div>\n   286→            <button\n   287→              type=\"button\"\n   288→              className=\"footer-terms-accept\"\n   289→              onClick={() => setShowTerms(false)}\n   290→            >\n   291→              I Understand\n   292→            </button>\n   293→          </div>\n   294→        </div>\n   295→      )}\n   296→\n   297→      {/* FAQ Modal */}\n   298→      {showFAQ && (\n   299→        <div className=\"footer-faq-overlay\">\n   300→          <div className=\"footer-faq-modal\" ref={faqModalRef}>\n   301→            <button\n   302→              type=\"button\"\n   303→              className=\"footer-faq-close\"\n   304→              onClick={() => setShowFAQ(false)}\n   305→            >\n   306→              ×\n   307→            </button>\n   308→            <h3 className=\"footer-faq-title\">Frequently Asked Questions</h3>\n   309→            <div className=\"footer-faq-content\">\n   310→              {faqSections.map((section) => (\n   311→                <div key={section.id} className=\"faq-section\">\n   312→                  <button\n   313→                    type=\"button\"\n   314→                    className={`faq-section-header ${expandedFAQ === section.id ? \"expanded\" : \"\"}`}\n   315→                    onClick={() => toggleFAQSection(section.id)}\n   316→                  >\n   317→                    <span className=\"faq-section-title\">{section.title}</span>\n   318→                    <span className=\"faq-section-arrow\">{expandedFAQ === section.id ? \"−\" : \"+\"}</span>\n   319→                  </button>\n   320→                  {expandedFAQ === section.id && (\n   321→                    <div className=\"faq-section-content\">\n   322→                      {section.content.split(\"\\n\\n\").map((paragraph, idx) => (\n   323→                        <p key={idx}>{paragraph}</p>\n   324→                      ))}\n   325→                    </div>\n   326→                  )}\n   327→                </div>\n   328→              ))}\n   329→            </div>\n   330→            <button\n   331→              type=\"button\"\n   332→              className=\"footer-faq-close-btn\"\n   333→              onClick={() => setShowFAQ(false)}\n   334→            >\n   335→              Close\n   336→            </button>\n   337→          </div>\n   338→        </div>\n   339→      )}\n   340→    </>\n   341→  );\n   342→}\n   343→\n   344→function AppContent() {\n   345→  const [chatExpanded, setChatExpanded] = useState(false);\n   346→  const [sidebarCollapsed, setSidebarCollapsed] = useState(false);\n   347→\n   348→  // Auto-apply referral code from localStorage after authentication\n   349→  useReferralApply();\n   350→\n   351→  const toggleSidebar = () => {\n   352→    setSidebarCollapsed(!sidebarCollapsed);\n   353→    document.body.classList.toggle(\"nc\", !sidebarCollapsed);\n   354→  };\n   355→\n   356→  return (\n   357→    <div className=\"app\">\n   358→      <BackgroundEffects />\n   359→\n   360→      {/* Fixed top bar */}\n   361→      <div className=\"top-bar\">\n   362→        <Header />\n   363→        <Ticker />\n   364→      </div>\n   365→\n   366→      {/* Fixed sidebar */}\n   367→      <Sidebar collapsed={sidebarCollapsed} onToggle={toggleSidebar} />\n   368→\n   369→      <main className=\"main\">\n   370→        <Routes>\n   371→          <Route path=\"/\" element={<HomePage />} />\n   372→          <Route path=\"/coinflip\" element={<RouteErrorBoundary label=\"Coinflip\"><CoinflipPage /></RouteErrorBoundary>} />\n   373→          <Route path=\"/coinflip/:matchId\" element={<RouteErrorBoundary label=\"Coinflip\"><CoinflipPage /></RouteErrorBoundary>} />\n   374→          <Route path=\"/lord-of-rngs\" element={<RouteErrorBoundary label=\"Lord of RNGs\"><LordOfRngsPage /></RouteErrorBoundary>} />\n   375→          <Route path=\"/lord-of-rngs/:matchId\" element={<RouteErrorBoundary label=\"Lord of RNGs\"><LordOfRngsPage /></RouteErrorBoundary>} />\n   376→          <Route path=\"/close-call\" element={<RouteErrorBoundary label=\"Close Call\"><CloseCallPage /></RouteErrorBoundary>} />\n   377→          <Route path=\"/crash\" element={<RouteErrorBoundary label=\"Crash\"><CryptoCrashPage /></RouteErrorBoundary>} />\n   378→          <Route path=\"/game-of-trades\" element={<RouteErrorBoundary label=\"Game of Trades\"><GameOfTradesPage /></RouteErrorBoundary>} />\n   379→          <Route path=\"/profile\" element={<RouteErrorBoundary label=\"Profile\"><ProfilePage /></RouteErrorBoundary>} />\n   380→          <Route path=\"/loot\" element={<RouteErrorBoundary label=\"Loot\"><LootPage /></RouteErrorBoundary>} />\n   381→          <Route path=\"/quests\" element={<RouteErrorBoundary label=\"Quests\"><QuestsPage /></RouteErrorBoundary>} />\n   382→          <Route path=\"/fairness\" element={<RouteErrorBoundary label=\"Fairness\"><FairnessPage /></RouteErrorBoundary>} />\n   383→          <Route path=\"/coinflip/:matchId/proof\" element={<RouteErrorBoundary label=\"Coinflip Proof\"><CoinflipRoundPage /></RouteErrorBoundary>} />\n   384→          <Route path=\"/lord-of-rngs/:matchId/proof\" element={<RouteErrorBoundary label=\"Lord of RNGs Proof\"><LordRoundPage /></RouteErrorBoundary>} />\n   385→          <Route path=\"/close-call/:roundId\" element={<RouteErrorBoundary label=\"Close Call Round\"><CloseCallRoundPage /></RouteErrorBoundary>} />\n   386→          <Route path=\"/r/:code\" element={<ReferralCapture />} />\n   387→          <Route path=\"*\" element={<NotFoundPage />} />\n   388→        </Routes>\n   389→        <Footer />\n   390→      </main>\n   391→\n   392→      <BuildBadge />\n   393→\n   394→      {/* Floating chat button */}\n   395→      <div className=\"chat-float\">\n   396→        <button type=\"button\" className=\"chat-float__btn\" onClick={() => setChatExpanded(!chatExpanded)}>\n   397→          <ChatIcon />\n   398→          <span className=\"chat-float__dot\" />\n   399→        </button>"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01W9CLkr9HqaEarze5DeMrDQ","session_id":"cad61997-ae30-4665-891e-0380cf7cb6d1","uuid":"bd545583-788c-40b5-a4cb-b8e0d08ad42f","timestamp":"2026-03-25T13:11:25.219Z"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Hnsvkv9GSJoyM7DUZgs1eX","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→import { useEffect, useRef } from \"react\";\n     2→import { useSession } from \"../../../context/SessionContext\";\n     3→import { useWallet } from \"@rng-utopia/wallet/hooks\";\n     4→import { applyReferralCode } from \"../../../lib/referral-api\";\n     5→\n     6→const STORAGE_KEY = \"referral_code\";\n     7→\n     8→/**\n     9→ * On authentication, if a referral code is stored in localStorage (from /r/:code),\n    10→ * auto-apply it via POST /referral/apply. Clears storage on success or permanent\n    11→ * failure (invalid code, already linked, self-referral). Keeps on transient failure\n    12→ * (network error) so it retries next auth.\n    13→ */\n    14→export function useReferralApply() {\n    15→  const { isAuthenticated, accessToken } = useSession();\n    16→  const { address } = useWallet();\n    17→  const appliedRef = useRef(false);\n    18→\n    19→  useEffect(() => {\n    20→    if (!isAuthenticated || !accessToken || !address) {\n    21→      appliedRef.current = false;\n    22→      return;\n    23→    }\n    24→\n    25→    // Prevent duplicate calls within the same auth session\n    26→    if (appliedRef.current) return;\n    27→\n    28→    let stored: string | null = null;\n    29→    try {\n    30→      stored = localStorage.getItem(STORAGE_KEY);\n    31→    } catch {\n    32→      // localStorage unavailable\n    33→      return;\n    34→    }\n    35→\n    36→    if (!stored) return;\n    37→\n    38→    let code: string;\n    39→    try {\n    40→      const parsed = JSON.parse(stored);\n    41→      code = parsed?.code;\n    42→    } catch {\n    43→      // Corrupt data — remove it\n    44→      try { localStorage.removeItem(STORAGE_KEY); } catch { /* noop */ }\n    45→      return;\n    46→    }\n    47→\n    48→    if (!code || typeof code !== \"string\") {\n    49→      try { localStorage.removeItem(STORAGE_KEY); } catch { /* noop */ }\n    50→      return;\n    51→    }\n    52→\n    53→    appliedRef.current = true;\n    54→\n    55→    applyReferralCode(accessToken, code)\n    56→      .then(() => {\n    57→        try { localStorage.removeItem(STORAGE_KEY); } catch { /* noop */ }\n    58→        // TODO: replace with toast notification when toast system is implemented\n    59→        console.warn(\"[referral] Referral code applied successfully\");\n    60→      })\n    61→      .catch((err: Error) => {\n    62→        const msg = err.message ?? \"\";\n    63→        // Permanent failures — code invalid, already linked, self-referral\n    64→        const isPermanent =\n    65→          msg.includes(\"ALREADY_LINKED\") ||\n    66→          msg.includes(\"SELF_REFERRAL\") ||\n    67→          msg.includes(\"NOT_FOUND\") ||\n    68→          msg.includes(\"INVALID\") ||\n    69→          msg.includes(\"already linked\") ||\n    70→          msg.includes(\"not found\") ||\n    71→          msg.includes(\"Cannot refer yourself\");\n    72→\n    73→        if (isPermanent) {\n    74→          try { localStorage.removeItem(STORAGE_KEY); } catch { /* noop */ }\n    75→        }\n    76→        // Transient failures (network, 500): keep localStorage for retry on next auth\n    77→      });\n    78→  }, [isAuthenticated, accessToken, address]);\n    79→}\n    80→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01W9CLkr9HqaEarze5DeMrDQ","session_id":"cad61997-ae30-4665-891e-0380cf7cb6d1","uuid":"7f0ac31f-fba8-4e72-8795-632d42d0a637","timestamp":"2026-03-25T13:11:25.103Z"}
